description: Join legendary jazz pianist, composer and educator Dr. Billy Taylor and his trio (Chip Jackson on bass and Winard Harper on drums) as they explore the styles and techniques of jazz performance, including blues, improvisation, swing, and the varied sounds and colors of the bass and drums. The trio performs jazz standards, including "Sweet Georgia Brown," "Laurentide Waltz," "Tricrotism," "Lover," and "Homage." (recorded in 2000 at C. D. Hylton High School in Woodbridge, VA).
